---

<Dossier slug="audit" cites={['C-0016', 'C-0017']}>
  <section class="section">
    <Figure id="C-0016" label="DoD REPORTED ASSETS, FY2025:" />
    <Annot>
      <AnnotLine key="In plain words">What the Pentagon says it owns — a figure its own auditors could not confirm.</AnnotLine>
      <ClaimRef id="C-0016" />
      <AnnotLine key="Source">DoD FY2025 Agency Financial Report · $4.7 tn reported liabilities</AnnotLine>
      <AnnotLine>The figure is reported, not audited.</AnnotLine>
    </Annot>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="label" style="margin-bottom:12px">CONSECUTIVE DISCLAIMERS OF OPINION:</div>
    <div class="figure-med">8</div>
    <Annot>
      <AnnotLine key="In plain words">The Pentagon has failed its audit eight years running — the only big agency that has never passed one.</AnnotLine>
      <ClaimRef id="C-0017" />
      <AnnotLine key="Span">FY2018 through FY2025 · 26 material weaknesses · 2 significant deficiencies</AnnotLine>
      <AnnotLine>Disclaimer of opinion: the books cannot support an opinion at all.</AnnotLine>
    </Annot>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="stack">
      <p class="body">The Department of Defense has received a disclaimer of opinion on its financial statements eight consecutive times, for every fiscal year from 2018 through 2025 (C-0017). It is the only major federal agency never to have passed an audit. A disclaimer is not a finding of loss; it is a finding that the records will not support any opinion, favorable or otherwise.</p>
      <p class="body">The fiscal year 2025 result carries 26 material weaknesses and two significant deficiencies. Among them, the auditors could not verify the existence and completeness of the F-35 Global Spares Pool, producing a material misstatement on the department's agency-wide statements. The reported asset base against which these weaknesses stand is $4.65 trillion (C-0016).</p>
      <p class="body">A statutory deadline now applies: the National Defense Authorization Act for fiscal year 2024 requires a clean audit by 31 December 2028 (C-0017). This file records the audit history as published. It draws no inference about the classified budget from the audit result, because none is available.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Dossier>
